  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dbb\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0d9c\u0dc4 \u0db8\u0dd0\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0db1\u0dc3\u0dad\u0dd2:\u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0dad\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The temple tree is also wild: it digs holes everywhere",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Agramatya Media Unit has complained to the Kollupitiya Police that the equipment from the media section of the Araliyagaha Mandir has been stolen.",
        "According to the Prime Minister's Media Division, two laptops, a video camera and other camera equipment were stolen from the media department.",
        "Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe did not move to Araliyagaha Mandir after assuming the office of Prime Minister and only a part of the Prime Minister's Media Unit was established in a building in Araliyagaha Mandir premises.",
        "The Prime Minister's Media Unit states that these equipments have been lost after the activists entered the temple building on the 9th.",
        "The Prime Minister's Media Unit also mentions that holes have been dug between the walls of the Araliyagaha Mandir, door locks have been broken and documents have been destroyed."
      ],
